<section id="methodology">
  <div class="center">
    <h1>Methodology</h1>
    <section class="agile-progressive-development">
      <h2>Agile Progressive Development</h2>
      <p class="lead-in">Through experience we’ve refined our process into the ultimate battle plan. We’ll assess your needs, divide the work into development sprints, and when the dust settles after our attack, we’ll be there for peace-keeping and maintenance.</p>
      <div class="assess trigger">
        <h3>Assess</h3>
        <div class="popover pop-left tertiary">
          <p>Our team has deep experience with nearly all development platforms. We’ll assess your needs and set you up with the right technology to rock the socks off of your competition.</p>
        </div>
      </div><!-- end of div.assess -->
      <div class="plan trigger">
        <h3>Plan</h3>
        <div class="popover pop-left">
          <p>At the beginning of each development sprint we’ll break the work down into manageable components. These are based on user stories, which describe planned functionality in a way any non-commando can understand.</p>
        </div>
      </div><!-- end of div.plan -->
      <div class="build-test-report trigger">
        <h3>Build &bull; Test &bull; Report</h3>
        <div class="popover">
          <p>Developers will take the user stories and turn them into site functionality. As they finish and test each story the work is passed to a crack squad of QA engineers for review.</p>
          <p>QA validates that the tests are executing successfully. If a feature isn’t performing, it’s rejected and sent back to development.</p>
          <p>Reports are compiled and updated throughout the sprint to keep the you up-to-date.</p>
        </div>
      </div><!-- end of div.build-test-report -->
      <div class="release trigger">
        <h3>Release</h3>
        <div class="popover pop-right">
          <p>The end of a sprint is marked by a milestone, a distinct set of features that can be released to the product.</p>
          <p>Milestones help keep the team focused on continuous release throughout the mission.</p>
        </div>
      </div><!-- end of div.release -->
      <div class="maintain trigger">
        <h3>Maintain</h3>
        <div class="popover pop-right tertiary">
          <p>We’re well equipped to provide superior maintenance for the products we build, or to step into a maintenance role for existing applications on most architectures and platforms.</p>
        </div>
      </div><!-- end of div.maintain -->
    </section><!-- end of section.agile-progressive-development -->
    <hr />
    <section class="team-structure">
      <h2>Team Structure</h2>
      <p class="lead-in">The right team structure is essential to any successful product. We’ve learned through experience which teams produce results and which ones don’t, and have continually refined our own to reflect this. Here’s how a typical squad works:</p>
      <div class="chief-technology-officer trigger">
        <h3>Chief Technology Officer</h3>
        <div class="popover-top">
          <p>Your battlefield commander, the CTO is responsible for technology architecture and strategy. They will ensure that the technology path is in line with business goals, keeping an eye on both the short and long term needs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="project-director trigger">
        <h3>Project Director</h3>
        <div class="popover-top">
          <p>The Project Director owns the project scope and plan, translating requirements into actionable items. They will set up realistic and achievable targets so the team can take responsibility and knock em’ down.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="project-manager trigger">
        <h3>Project Manager</h3>
        <div class="popover-top">
          <p>Tactical coordination is the domain of the Project Manager.  From day-to-day and sprint-to-sprint tracking and facilitation, the PM ensures that team members aren't blocked and that process is running smoothly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="developers trigger">
        <h3>Developers</h3>
        <div class="popover-top">
          <p>Our agile coding machines. They develop stories and functionality to spec, perform code reviews, and work together to overcome blocks and onboard new resources.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="qa-lead-and-engineers trigger">
        <h3>QA Lead/Engineers</h3>
        <div class="popover-top">
          <p>The ultimate in test-driven automators. Documentation, execution, and automation of stories and workflows are their speciality. Developers fear their wrath.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="product-owner trigger">
        <h3>Product Owner</h3>
        <div class="popover-top tertiary">
          <p>You own the product vision. We’ll set you up to work closely with the team throughout development sprints, providing constant key feedback on each story to ensure that the deliverables are squarely in line with expectations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section><!-- end of section.team-structure -->
  </div><!-- end of div.center -->
</section>

<section id="product-delivery">
  <div class="center">
    <h1>Product Delivery</h1>
    <h2 class="first trigger"><span>Strategic Assessment</span></h2>
    <div class="popover-top strategic-assessment tertiary">
      <p>Our teams have deep knowledge of nearly all operating platforms, including Windows, Solaris, Linux, and every flavor of BSD. We have experience designing and building systems to run on the cloud, so that the applications can easily scale on demand as the business grows.</p>
      <p>Whether you’re looking for a completely new build, or for someone to freshen up your existing platform, we have the extensive knowledge required to assess and correct your mission-critical software.</p>
    </div>
    <h2 class="trigger"><span>Agile Development</span></h2>
    <div class="popover-top agile-development tertiary">
      <p>Janeiro Digital is a tactical expert in the Agile Development process. We’re well-versed in Web 2.0, Social Networking, Distributed Networking, Backend Systems, and Service Oriented Architecture.</p>
      <p>Our agile, scrum-based development methodology has been specifically tailored for working with dispersed teams. From early concept and design to architecture, implementation, testing, and launch, we offer our clients everything they need to go from idea to successful product.</p>
    </div>
    <h2 class="trigger"><span>Quality Assurance</span></h2>
    <div class="popover-top quality-assurance tertiary">
      <p>Our quality assurance teams utilize industry best practices, proven toolkits, and cutting edge methods such as community-based testing to deliver valuable and rapid results that will quickly nuke bugs, stability problems, and performance issues.</p>
    </div>
    <h2 class="last trigger"><span>Strategic Maintenance</span></h2>
    <div class="popover-top strategic-maintenance tertiary">
      <p>The ability to maintain and manage applications and systems is a critical void that has become a nuisance for most instead of a competitive advantage. To combat this issue, Janeior Digital has  created a strategic maintenance program that aligns your business needs with resources capable of taking over this task.</p>
      <p>We’re well-equipped to step into a maintenance role for existing applications on most architectures and platforms, allowing you to keep your in-house developers focused on knocking down the competition. We offer all aspects of application maintenance services, from bug filing and tracking to full fledged customer support.</p>
    </div>
  </div><!-- end of div.center -->
</section>

